The tale of
"Kitty-in-Boots" was referenced
in an out-of-print

06:51.945 --> 06:56.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
biography on the author. Three
manuscripts
were then found in the Victoria
and Albert

06:56.750 --> 06:58.618 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Museum archive in London.

06:58.718 --> 07:05.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Her classic "Peter Rabbit" has
been published
in 36 languages, and sold more
than 45 million

07:05.558 --> 07:10.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
copies. Beatrix Potter had only
completed
a single drawing to go with
"Kitty-in-Boots."

07:11.064 --> 07:14.034 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The rest will be created by
illustrator Quentin
Blake.

07:14.134 --> 07:17.704 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICIA ROUTLEDGE, Beatrix
Potter Society:
I mean, it will go like a hot
cake. It's tantalizing,

07:17.804 --> 07:21.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but, of course, the announcement
has been
made now.

07:22.075 --> 07:28.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHARON THOMAS: This July marks
the 150th anniversary
of Beatrix Potter's birth. The
tale of "Kitty-in-Boots"

07:28.848 --> 07:31.017 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will be published in September.

07:31.117 --> 07:36.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And the story
that started
it all, "The Tale of Peter
Rabbit," was first

07:36.323 --> 07:39.359 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
published in 1902.

