Still to come on the "NewsHour":
an end to
solitary confinement for
juveniles; the fine

08:16.763 --> 08:22.869 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
line between promoting security
and fear on
the campaign trail; a push for
an alternative

08:22.969 --> 08:36.483 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to college; and much more.

08:36.583 --> 08:41.421 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In the latter part of his
tenure, President
Obama has put criminal justice
reform high

08:41.521 --> 08:43.390 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on his agenda.

08:43.490 --> 08:49.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His latest move includes a new
ban on solitary
confinement for juveniles in the
federal prison

08:49.562 --> 08:55.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
system. The executive actions
also put new
limits on how long federal
prison officials

08:55.168 --> 08:58.304 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
