years in solitary
at Rikers Island.

09:30.069 --> 09:33.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the op-ed, the president says
-- quote
-- "Solitary confinement has the
potential

09:33.807 --> 09:38.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to lead to devastating, lasting
psychological
consequences. The United States
is a nation

09:38.978 --> 09:44.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of second chances, but the
experience of solitary
confinement too often undercuts
that second

09:44.150 --> 09:45.919 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
chance."

09:46.019 --> 09:49.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We discuss these changes with
Shaka Senghor,
who was convicted of
second-degree murder

09:49.155 --> 09:53.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and sent to prison at the age of
19, and during
parts of his sentence, he spent
a total of

09:53.927 --> 10:00.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
seven years in solitary. He's
written a memoir
and is with the group #Cut50, a
national bipartisan

10:00.200 --> 10:05.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
initiative to reduce the prison
population.
And Maurice Chammah of The
Marshall Project,

10:05.672 --> 10:09.242 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
